Etymology[edit]

ex- +‎ prōprius +‎ -ō

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ekˈsproː.pri.oː/, [ɛkˈs̠pɾoː.pɾi.oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ekˈspro.pri.o/, [ɛkˈsprɔː.pri.ɔ]
  • (Vulgar) IPA(key): /esˈproː.pri.oː/, [esˈpro.prʲ.o]

Verb[edit]

exprōpriō (present infinitive exprōpriāre, perfect active exprōpriāvī, supine exprōpriātum); first conjugation

  1. (Medieval Latin) I expropriate.
